All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Authtoken
An Authtoken is used to identify a User after a successful login
AuthtokenDao
Inserts, queries, updates, and deletes Authtokens
ClearResult
Result of the requested clear, which removes all data from the Database
ClearService
Used to attempt to clear the all data in the Database
DataAccessException
Exception thrown when an error occurs upon attempting to access data
Event
An Event constitutes a significant place and date for a Person for a specified reason
EventDao
Inserts, queries, updates, and deletes Events
EventRequest
Used when requesting a single Event associated with the current User
EventResult
Result of the requested single Event with the specified ID
EventService
Used to attempt to find the Event specified in the request
FamilyEventRequest
Used when requesting all Events for every member of the current User's tree
FamilyEventResult
Result of the requested Events for every member of the current User's tree
FamilyEventService
Used to attempt to find the Events of the entire tree of the current User
FamilyRequest
Used when requesting all Persons for every member of the current User's tree
FamilyResult
Result of the requested Persons for every member of the family tree of the current User's tree
FamilyService
Used to attempt to find the entire tree of the current User
FillRequest
Used to fill in a tree of 'Persons' for the current 'User'
FillResult
Result of the requested fill for the current 'User's' tree
FillService
Used to attempt to fill a given amount of generations of the tree for the User specified in the Request
LoadRequest
Used to load the provided 'User', 'Person', and 'Event' data into the database
LoadResult
Result of the requested load of 'User', 'Person', and 'Event' data into the Database
LoadService
Used to clear all data from the Database and subsequently load the User, Person, and Event data from the Request into the Database
LoginRequest
Used when requesting a login for the specified username and password
LoginResult
Result of the requested login for the specified username and password, including a generated authtoken
LoginService
Used to attempt to log in the User specified in the request
Person
A Person represents a life and its connections to others
PersonDao
Inserts, queries, updates, and deletes Persons
PersonRequest
Used when requesting a single Person associated with the current User
PersonResult
Result of the requested single Person with the specified ID
PersonService
Used to attempt to find the Person specified in the request
RegisterRequest
Used when registering a new User
RegisterResult
Result of the requested register for a new 'User'
RegisterService
Used to attempt to create a new User specified in the request
User
A User is an entity recognized internally used to identify a login
UserDao
Inserts, queries, updates, and deletes Users
